            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with any remaining oil</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>pepper</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!) and cook for 3-4 min or until fragrant</p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli relish</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> – this is your <strong>sticky chilli sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
